{
  "texts": [
    "In this work, the authors tackle several challenges related to the application of RL techniques to the context of green datacenters.",
    "The first issue relates to the environment.",
    "The dynamic of green data center environments makes the scheduling process difficult as it has to consider and manage the intermittent and variable nature of renewable energy sources.",
    "Moreover, the lack of uniformity in the environments makes it challenging to compare different approaches.",
    "The second challenge highlights the absence of discussion regarding the systems design choices effect (e.g., the planning horizon size)."
  ]
}